CHELICERAE. Beige-brown, long and slender (
Fig. 2B, F
), without apophysis and gland openings. Lengths of basal article, distal article and movable finger, 0.99, 1.19 and 0.37, respectively. Basal segment basally and terminally widened. Distal segment distally enlarged, frontally evenly set with long bristles, the longest ones shorter than the article diameter. Fixed finger with a series of 21, movable finger with 23 diaphanous teeth.

CHELICERAE. As in male, more robust (
Fig. 4C
). Lengths of basal article, distal article and movable finger 1.01, 1.19 and 0.48, respectively.
